race.comment: RAYMOND'S REWARD (4) has ample early speed and draws to advantage on the inside. Fourth-up and peaking now, he should roll straight to the front and prove very hard to reel in. GRINZINGER ACE (1) had excuses last start when beaten a long way, but his prior form reads strongly for this grade. Three weeks between runs, he's capable of bouncing back sharply. IRONBAR (3) was an eye-catcher here two back and strips fitter again. A repeat of that run has him right in the finish. IN THAT MODE (2) didn't fire a shot fresh but is a likely improver that will appreciate getting out over further. Watch for him running on late.
